title: Foward ORT error messages on the C-ABI to exceptions thrown in winml
body:
When layering was done, errors that occur on the c-abi boundary that are wrapped by OrtStatuses were not forwarded properly to winml exceptions, and only the translated HRESULT was surfaced, and not the message.

Fix: When a failing c-abi call is made, the RETURN_HR_IF_NOT_OK_MSG macro needs to set an issue an originateerror call to save the error string at the point of failure. The corresponding throw that occurs downstream needs to reuse that error message when creating the exception. This is done by calling winrt::hresult_error with from_abi_t, which will check to get the error message from there instead of clobbering it.

body:
**Describe the bug**
When trying to use the DirectML provider a crash happens when calling `DMLCreateDevice1` [here](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/33b5010e624d0c649e121a323eda29dfa4074e2a/onnxruntime/core/providers/dml/dml_provider_factory.cc#L120-L123). Replacing it with `DMLCreateDevice` works although I don't know if there are any unintended consequences:
```cpp
THROW_IF_FAILED(DMLCreateDevice(d3d12_device.Get(),
                              flags,
                              IID_PPV_ARGS(&dml_device)));
```

**Urgency**
DirectML does not work (for me) without that fix. For me personally not having DML is a big issue as I need my program to run on all GPU vendors' devices.

**System information**
- OS Platform and Distribution (e.g., Linux Ubuntu 16.04): Windows 10 Pro 1903
- ONNX Runtime installed from (source or binary): source with use_dml, build_wheel
- ONNX Runtime version: 1.2.0 (current master)
- Python version: 3.7.3
- Visual Studio version (if applicable): 2019
- GCC/Compiler version (if compiling from source): -
- CUDA/cuDNN version: -
- GPU model and memory: GTX 1070 (8gb)

**To Reproduce**
Build onnxruntime with `build.bat --config RelWithDebInfo --parallel --use_dml --cmake_generator "Visual Studio 16 2019`. Try adding the DML provider (eg. start with [this sample](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/csharp/test/Microsoft.ML.OnnxRuntime.EndToEndTests.Capi/C_Api_Sample.cpp) and add `OrtSessionOptionsAppendExecutionProvider_DML(session_options, 0);`. The program will crash at this line (although I noticed when using a nonsensical device like 100 it goes through, but seems to use CPU still).
Alternatively, python can be used using [my recent PR](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/3359) and the following code will crash without a message at `set_providers()`:

```python
import onnxruntime as rt
session_opts = rt.SessionOptions()
session_opts.enable_mem_pattern = False
session = rt.InferenceSession("model.onnx", session_opts)
session.set_providers(["DmlExecutionProvider"])
```

**Expected behavior**
It should not crash and use the DirectML execution provider.

title: Custom ops with same name and different Execution Provider
body:
Hi,
My need is to use custom ops API to implement my custom op both for CPU Execution Provider and CUDA Execution Provider and having these implementations on a single separate shared library.

Thanks to [this fix](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/3165) I was able to implement and register my custom op with CUDA Execution Provider implementation (i.e. implementing GetExecutionProvider() function returning "CUDAExecutionProvider").
But when I try to register another custom op with the same name but for CPU Execution Provider (i.e. GetExecutionProvider() left default), I run into this error: 

Trying to register schema with name custom_op_one ... but it is already registered ..."  (schema_registry.cc : 66).

I think the problem is because in CreateCustomRegistry() function from custom_ops.cc, a schema is always added for each custom operator.
My workaround was to modify this code and only add the schema if not already added.
Then it is working fine and the good kernel of my operator is called depending on the EP asked for the session (CUDA or CPU)

Does it make sense to you and would you plan adding this feature?

Best Regards  / Thanks.
